    note right of Unconnected
        Socket created without host/port.
        bind() can be called once (transitions to Bound).
        connect() moves directly to Connected.
        setReceiveBufferSize() must be called before connect() for large windows.
    end note

    note right of Connected
        shutdownInput() and shutdownOutput() are self-loops;
        they modify half-close state but socket remains Connected.
        getInputStream() fails if input was shut down.
        getOutputStream() fails if output was shut down.
        setPerformancePreferences() has no effect after connection.
    end note

    note right of Closed
        Terminal state. Cannot reconnect or rebind.
        close() is idempotent.
        Some query methods (getInetAddress, getPort, etc.) still work.
        getInputStream, getOutputStream, setOption, getOption throw IOException.
    end note
